    {
      "content": "Manage your StorSimple bandwidth templates | Microsoft Azure",
      "pos": [
        27,
        87
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Describes how to manage StorSimple bandwidth templates, which allow you to control bandwidth consumption.",
      "pos": [
        105,
        210
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Use the StorSimple Manager service to manage StorSimple bandwidth templates",
      "pos": [
        490,
        565
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Overview",
      "pos": [
        570,
        578
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Bandwidth templates allow you to configure multiple time-of-day schedules to tier the data from the StorSimple device to the cloud.",
      "pos": [
        580,
        711
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can also create, modify, delete, and save these schedules as templates.",
      "pos": [
        712,
        787
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "These bandwidth templates can then be applied across volume containers to control the bandwidth consumed by your StorSimple device when performing operations that involve the cloud.",
      "pos": [
        788,
        969
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Depending on your bandwidth usage pattern, you can also choose from a list of default templates.",
      "pos": [
        970,
        1066
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "With bandwidth throttling schedules you can:",
      "pos": [
        1068,
        1112
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Specify schedules that customize bandwidth usage depending on the workloads.",
      "pos": [
        1116,
        1192
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Centralize management and reuse the schedules across multiple devices in an easy and seamless manner.",
      "pos": [
        1196,
        1297
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This feature is available only for StorSimple physical devices and not for virtual devices.",
      "pos": [
        1299,
        1390
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "All the bandwidth templates for your service are displayed in a tabular format, and contain the following information:",
      "pos": [
        1391,
        1509
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        1513,
        1593
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Name<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> – A unique name assigned to the bandwidth template when it was created."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        1597,
        1676
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Schedule<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> – The number of schedules contained in a given bandwidth template."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
